    "z07_faq": {
      "type": "custom-liquid",
      "settings": {
        "section_visibility": "always",
        "custom_liquid": "<script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n{\n  \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n  \"@type\": \"FAQPage\",\n  \"mainEntity\": [\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"What makes Z07 different from a conventional hybrid IEM?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Z07 uses a tube-free, filter-free acoustic chamber instead of routing sound through long tubes and dampers. A true 3-way crossover helps the seven drivers blend cleanly, so bass, vocals, and treble arrive with better focus and less haze.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"Why does fit matter so much for Z07?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Fit affects what you hear. A stable seal helps Z07 keep its intended bass pressure, center image, and stage focus. FitMorph gives listeners multiple outer-fit options so the monitor can settle faster before the sound is judged.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"What is FitMorph?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"FitMorph is AAW's adaptive fit system for Z07. The same Z07 tuning works across interchangeable FitMorph options, letting the listener choose shark-fin stability, a cleaner compact fit, or optional custom outer-ear support.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"Will the custom FitMorph fit option change the sound?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"The optional custom FitMorph option changes how Z07 rests in the outer ear, not the sound you chose. The canal still seals with LiquidMorph silicone ear tips, so the goal is a more secure fit while keeping the same Z07 tuning.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"How many drivers does Z07 use?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Z07 uses seven drivers in total: one 10mm titanium diaphragm dynamic driver for bass and six balanced armatures for midrange, highs, and air.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"Is Z07 suitable for stage monitoring?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Yes. Z07 is designed for critical monitoring and long-session professional use. The shark-fin FitMorph option improves stability for stage work, while final suitability still depends on personal fit, isolation needs, and monitoring level.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"Is Z07 easy to drive?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Z07 has 12 Ohm impedance and 101dB sensitivity, so it can be driven by portable players and phone dongles. A clean, low-output-impedance source is recommended for best noise control.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"What is the difference between the two included FitMorph fit options?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"The shark-fin option gives stronger outer-ear lock-in for stability. The finless option gives a cleaner contour with less pressure, which can be better for smaller ears or relaxed listening.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"Can Z07 be customized like a custom IEM?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Z07 remains a universal monitor, but an optional custom FitMorph fit option can be made from an outer-ear impression. It customizes how Z07 rests in the outer ear while the canal still seals with silicone ear tips.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"What cable connector does Z07 use?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Z07 uses a 0.78mm 2-pin connection integrated with the FitMorph fit system. It gives listeners a more reassuring long-term cable connection while keeping the Z07 sound intact.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"Does Z07 come with a warranty?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Yes. Z07 includes a 1-year warranty covering manufacturing defects under normal use. For support, contact AAW Singapore or the authorized dealer where you purchased it.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"Where can I demo AAW Z07 in Singapore?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"In Singapore, you can start with AAW Office, Zeppelin & Co., JABEN, or AV One. For demo, support, warranty, or dealer questions, contact AAW Singapore at sales@acousticwerkes.com or +65-8731-5476.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"@type\": \"Question\",\n      \"name\": \"Can I buy Z07 outside Singapore?\",\n      \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n        \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n        \"text\": \"Yes. Outside Singapore, AAW works with specialist audio stores and listening rooms across Hong Kong, Macau, Japan, China, South Korea, and Thailand. Use the store locator to find the closest authorized listening point or dealer.\"\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n</script><div class=\"z07-feature-shell\"><section class=\"z07-section\"><div class=\"z07-wrap z07-grid-2\"><div><p class=\"z07-kicker\">FAQ</p><h2>Frequently asked questions about Z07</h2><p>A short version for listeners comparing Z07 with conventional hybrid IEMs, stage monitors, and adaptive-fit systems.</p></div><div class=\"z07-faq-list\"><details class=\"z07-faq-item\"><summary><span>What makes Z07 different from a conventional hybrid IEM?</span><b>-</b></summary><p>Z07 uses a tube-free, filter-free acoustic chamber instead of routing sound through long tubes and dampers. A true 3-way crossover helps the seven drivers blend cleanly, so bass, vocals, and treble arrive with better focus and less haze.</p></details><details class=\"z07-faq-item\"><summary><span>Why does fit matter so much for Z07?</span><b>+</b></summary><p>Fit affects what you hear. A stable seal helps Z07 keep its intended bass pressure, center image, and stage focus. FitMorph gives listeners multiple outer-fit options so the monitor can settle faster before the sound is judged.</p></details><details class=\"z07-faq-item\"><summary><span>What is FitMorph?</span><b>+</b></summary><p>FitMorph is AAW's adaptive fit system for Z07. The same Z07 tuning works across interchangeable FitMorph options, letting the listener choose shark-fin stability, a cleaner compact fit, or optional custom outer-ear support.</p></details><details class=\"z07-faq-item\"><summary><span>Will the custom FitMorph fit option change the sound?</span><b>+</b></summary><p>The optional custom FitMorph option changes how Z07 rests in the outer ear, not the sound you chose. The canal still seals with LiquidMorph silicone ear tips, so the goal is a more secure fit while keeping the same Z07 tuning.</p></details><details class=\"z07-faq-item\"><summary><span>How many drivers does Z07 use?</span><b>+</b></summary><p>Z07 uses seven drivers in total: one 10mm titanium diaphragm dynamic driver for bass and six balanced armatures for midrange, highs, and air.</p></details><details class=\"z07-faq-item\"><summary><span>Is Z07 suitable for stage monitoring?</span><b>+</b></summary><p>Yes. Z07 is designed for critical monitoring and long-session professional use. The shark-fin FitMorph option improves stability for stage work, while final suitability still depends on personal fit, isolation needs, and monitoring level.</p></details><details class=\"z07-faq-item\"><summary><span>Is Z07 easy to drive?</span><b>+</b></summary><p>Z07 has 12 Ohm impedance and 101dB sensitivity, so it can be driven by portable players and phone dongles. A clean, low-output-impedance source is recommended for best noise control.</p></details><details class=\"z07-faq-item\"><summary><span>What is the difference between the two included FitMorph fit options?</span><b>+</b></summary><p>The shark-fin option gives stronger outer-ear lock-in for stability. The finless option gives a cleaner contour with less pressure, which can be better for smaller ears or relaxed listening.</p></details><details class=\"z07-faq-item\"><summary><span>Can Z07 be customized like a custom IEM?</span><b>+</b></summary><p>Z07 remains a universal monitor, but an optional custom FitMorph fit option can be made from an outer-ear impression. It customizes how Z07 rests in the outer ear while the canal still seals with silicone ear tips.</p></details><details class=\"z07-faq-item\"><summary><span>What cable connector does Z07 use?</span><b>+</b></summary><p>Z07 uses a 0.78mm 2-pin connection integrated with the FitMorph fit system. It gives listeners a more reassuring long-term cable connection while keeping the Z07 sound intact.</p></details><details class=\"z07-faq-item\"><summary><span>Does Z07 come with a warranty?</span><b>+</b></summary><p>Yes. Z07 includes a 1-year warranty covering manufacturing defects under normal use. For support, contact AAW Singapore or the authorized dealer where you purchased it.</p></details><details class=\"z07-faq-item\"><summary><span>Where can I demo AAW Z07 in Singapore?</span><b>+</b></summary><p>In Singapore, you can start with AAW Office, Zeppelin & Co., JABEN, or AV One. For demo, support, warranty, or dealer questions, contact AAW Singapore at sales@acousticwerkes.com or +65-8731-5476.</p></details><details class=\"z07-faq-item\"><summary><span>Can I buy Z07 outside Singapore?</span><b>+</b></summary><p>Yes. Outside Singapore, AAW works with specialist audio stores and listening rooms across Hong Kong, Macau, Japan, China, South Korea, and Thailand. Use the store locator to find the closest authorized listening point or dealer.</p></details></div></div></section></div><script>(function(){function initZ07Faq(){document.querySelectorAll('.z07-faq-item').forEach(function(item){var mark=item.querySelector('summary b');function sync(){if(mark)mark.textContent=item.open?'-':'+';}item.addEventListener('toggle',sync);sync();});}if(document.readyState==='loading')document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded',initZ07Faq);else initZ07Faq();})();</script>",
